    "plan_content": "Here's a summary of my findings and the plan:\n\n## Plan: `uv cache stats` Subcommand\n\nI explored the codebase across 4 key files. The implementation touches exactly 4 files (3 edits, 1 new file):\n\n### Changes at a glance\n\n| # | File | Change |\n|---|------|--------|\n| 1 | `crates/uv-cli/src/lib.rs` | Add `Stats(StatsArgs)` to `CacheCommand` enum + `StatsArgs` struct |\n| 2 | `crates/uv/src/commands/cache_stats.rs` | **New file** — `cache_stats()` implementation |\n| 3 | `crates/uv/src/commands/mod.rs` | `mod cache_stats` + `pub(crate) use cache_stats::cache_stats` |\n| 4 | `crates/uv/src/lib.rs` | Dispatch arm for `CacheCommand::Stats` |\n\n### Implementation notes from exploration\n\n- **`CacheBucket::iter()`** yields 10 buckets: `Wheels`, `SourceDistributions`, `FlatIndex`, `Git`, `Interpreter`, `Simple`, `Archive`, `Builds`, `Environments`, `Binaries`. The `Python` variant exists in the enum but is **not** in `iter()` — the plan follows `iter()` as specified.\n- **Display** for `CacheBucket` delegates to `to_str()`, producing versioned names like `wheels-v6`, `sdists-v9`, etc.\n- **`cache_stats`** will have no preview gate (unlike `cache_size`) and takes only `(cache, human_readable, printer)` — no `globals.preview`.\n- Each bucket path is checked with `.exists()` before measuring, so empty/missing buckets print `0` cleanly.\n- `diskus::DiskUsage::new(vec![path]).count_ignoring_errors()` — same approach as `cache_size.rs`.",
